= SDL_SaveBMP_RW =
Use this function to save a surface to a seekable SDL data source (memory or file).


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_SaveBMP_RW(SDL_Surface* surface,
                   SDL_RWops*   dst,
                   int          freedst)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''surface'''
|a pointer to the [[SDL_Surface]] to be saved
|-
|'''dst'''
|a pointer to a data source to save to
|-
|'''freedst'''
|non-zero to close the source ''(should this be dst instead of src?)'' after being written
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 0 on success or a negative error code on failure; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

